body:
The following minimized test case passes in most tools, but fails in Verilator built from head, master branch:

```verilog
module regfile (
  input  logic       clock,
  output logic[31:0] out,
  input  logic[7:0]  addr
);

  logic[31:0] data_[256];
  logic[31:0] out_;

  always_ff @(posedge clock) begin
    tick(addr);
  end

  task automatic tick(logic[7:0] addr);
    data_[addr] <= 1;
    out_ <= data_[addr];
  endtask

  always_comb out = out_;

endmodule
```

Test run in Ubuntu 22.04.3 on x86_64:

```console
aappleby@jankytron:~$ verilator --version
Verilator 5.019 devel rev v5.018-85-gc5ba6e22f
aappleby@jankytron:~$ verilator --cc verilator_bad_regfile.sv
%Error: Internal Error: verilator_bad_regfile.sv:15:17: ../V3EmitCFunc.h:1408: Unknown node type reached emitter: BEGIN
   15 |     data_[addr] <= 1;
      |                 ^~
                        ... See the manual at https://verilator.org/verilator_doc.html for more assistance.
```

I'll attempt to fix it myself.
